headlines.description: — Nikola Vucevic had 22 points and 13 rebounds, Zach LaVine added 25 points and the Chicago Bulls beat the Brooklyn Nets 115-107 on Sunday to snap a six-game losing streak.

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at LA Clippers

headlines.description: — Marcus Morris scored 22 points and the Los Angeles Clippers dominated the short-handed Lakers in a 104-86 victory on Sunday to end a two-game skid.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers rout short-handed Lakers 104-86, end 2-game skid

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum had 22 points and eight rebounds, and the Boston Celtics blew past the short-handed Charlotte Hornets 116-86 on Sunday.

— Grayson Allen had 11 of his 15 points during a game-changing third quarter, lifting the Memphis Grizzlies to a 116-100 victory Sunday night over the short-handed Philadelphia 76ers, who were without All-Star center Joel Embiid.
headlines.shortLinkText: Allen helps lead Grizzlies past short-handed 76ers

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Atlanta Hawks

headlines.description: — Clint Capela had 24 points and 18 rebounds, Danilo Gallinari scored 25 points and the Atlanta Hawks beat the Golden State Warriors 117-111 Sunday night for their third straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Capela, Gallinari pace Hawks to third straight victory

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Lonzo Ball had 27 points and a career-high eight 3-pointers, and the New Orleans Pelicans beat the Houston Rockets 122-115 on Sunday night to end a two-game skid.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ball makes career-best 8 3s as Pelicans beat Rockets 122-115

headlines.description: — Aaron Gordon scored 24 points against his former team, rallying the Denver Nuggets past the Orlando Magic 119-109 Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Aaron Gordon's 24 points leads Denver past Orlando 119-109
